You are editing UI surface area. Before running `conductor ship`:

1. Update the "브라우저 체크리스트" section in `.work/{KEY}.md` to reflect
   the screens / interactions you changed. A checklist with zero items is
   treated as missing — ship will refuse.
2. Cursor has no browser automation tool. To satisfy Phase 1.5 UI
   verification you must choose one of:
   - `--ui-verify <gif-path>` — you or the user performs a manual run and
     attaches the GIF.
   - `--skip-ui-check "<reason>"` — requires an explicit reason; the MR
     body records it.
   - Install `@conductor-kit/ui-verify` (Playwright) — the CLI drives a
     headless browser and produces the GIF itself.
3. Never hard-code strings in a View/Component. Use the project's i18n
   hook (if `src/i18n/**` exists, it is almost certainly required). Scan
   the existing file before adding text.
4. Prefer re-using existing components over adding new ones. Before
   creating a new `*.vue` / `*.tsx` under `src/components/`, grep for
   something similar.
